<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ten Police Officers Enter Jericho Amid Riots </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ten Police Officers Enter Jericho Amid Riots </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1105112394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 11 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1105112394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ten Palestinian police officers entered Jericho 
today via the Allenby Bridge. Our correspondent Moti Amir 
reports that the officers are slated to take over the local 
police station today. IDF [Israel Defense Forces] officers in 
the area ordered the soldiers to evacuate the hundreds of 
residents who waited for the policemen in the city square and to 
close the shops in the city. A riot erupted in the area, and IDF 
officers forcefully evacuated correspondents and journalists, 
including a Qol Yisra'el crew. Three officers dragged Qol 
Yisra'el's correspondent for about 20 meters, and shouted and 
threatened him with loaded guns, causing him slight bruises. 
The residents of Jericho started to riot, forcing IDF officers 
to disperse them with rubber bullets. 

</TEXT>

