<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Efforts Continuing To Resolve Cabinet Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Efforts Continuing To Resolve Cabinet Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1105114294 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1030 GMT 11 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1105114294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] There have been no new developments in the 
government crisis. Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri is spending 
his fourth day at home in Quraytim today. His visitors report 
that he is persisting with his positions, which call for 
broadening the basis of government representation of Christian 
leaders. The visitors appealed to him to start exercising his 
powers again and to maintain his authority. 
  Within the framework of the efforts to solve this crisis, 
former Prime Minister 'Umar Karami is now meeting with Chamber 
of Deputies Speaker Nabih Birri. 
  Delegations continued to arrive at Prime Minister 
al-Hariri's 
house in Quraytim, where he received Labor Minister 'Abdallah 
al-Amin, Minister of State Shahe Barsoumian, and Deputy Khatchig 
Babikian. Earlier, al-Hariri received al-Mina' Mayor 
'Abd-al-Qadir 'Alam-al-Din, who expressed his support for him in 
continuing to shoulder responsibility. He also received a 
delegation from the al-Fulayti clan in 'Irsal, which called on 
al-Hariri to continue shouldering his responsibility. He then 
met a delegation led by Shaykh Khalil al-Mays, the mufti of 
Zahlah and al-Biqa. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

