<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salih Orders Reconstruction of Destroyed Houses </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Orders Reconstruction of Destroyed Houses </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1205054794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1205054794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pursuant to instructions from brother Lieutenant 
General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Presidential 
Council, Shaykh 'Abd-al-Majid al-Zandani yesterday visited the 
families of the victims of the spiteful missile aggression. He 
extended condolences on behalf of the brother president. 
  Shaykh 'Abd-al-Majid al-Zandani had earlier inspected the 
situation of the people at the site of the ugly, odious crime 
committed by the forces of apostasy and secession when a missile 
fell on the homes of secure citizens. 
  The Yemeni News Agency, SABA', has learned that brother Lt. 
Gen. 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih has instructed the competent 
authorities to reconstruct the houses that were destroyed at the 
expense of the state, and to give 100,000 riyals in aid to each 
affected family. 

</TEXT>

