headquarters of the 18th and 95th Brigades east of Qal'at Salih 
and started fires in these two headquarters. The statement said 
that the attacking forces killed at least 50 Ba'thist soldiers. 
Among them were the commander of the artillery battalion, named 
'Aziz, and the intelligence officer, 'Ali Salman Habib. The 
statement added that our Mujahidin succeeded in setting fire to 
one of the oil wells in al-'Amarah. 

