<H3> <TI>   Harvester, Tractor Shipment Arrives 11 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Harvester, Tractor Shipment Arrives 11 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1205164194 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1030 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1205164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Staff General Husayn Kamil Hasan, minister of 
industry and minerals, has announced the arrival of a ship on 11 
May, carrying 236 harvesters and a number of tractors. 
  In a statement to INA, he said these harvesters and tractors 
will be immediately distributed by a specialized committee to 
farmers in all the country's governorates. They will be used in 
the current agricultural and harvest campaign. 
  Staff Gen. Husayn Kamil Hasan said the Ministry of Industry 
and Minerals and the industrial sectors have always been the 
first to support the agricultural sector, with equipment, 
requirements, fertilizers, and pesticides, with the objective of 
developing agriculture, increasing production in our country, 
and improving its quality. 
  He said all this is pursuant to the instructions of leader 
President Saddam Husayn, may God watch over him, and his 
excellency's continuous care for developing the agricultural 
sector and for increasing its capacity and capabilities in order 
to secure abundant food for our lofty Iraqi people and to break 
the blockade imposed by the unjust ones on our struggler 
country. May God grant us success to serve our people under the 
leadership of the architect of Iraq's glory, leader President 
Saddam Husayn, may God preserve him. 
  A shipment of harvesters and tractors arrived earlier this 
year, and was distributed to farmers. Other shipments of 
harvesters and tractors will arrive later. 

</TEXT>

