<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Demands Power Transfer in All of West Bank </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Demands Power Transfer in All of West Bank </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1205183194 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1205183194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yasir 'Arafat is demanding that Israel immediately 
transfer to the Palestinians self-government powers in all of 
the West Bank. 'Arafat raised this demand during his meeting 
with President 'Ezer Weizman in Pretoria. This was learned by 
our correspondent 'Imanu'el Halperin. Prime Minister Rabin was 
briefed about this development. 
  The Swiss president, who also met with Mr. Weizman in South 
Africa, proposed to establish a sixth committee in the framework 
of the multilateral talks. His proposal calls for establishing 
a committee to deal with human rights in the region. The 
deliberations of this committee would be coordinated by 
Switzerland. Israel will examine the proposal. 

</TEXT>

