<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Partial List of National Authority Members Released </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Partial List of National Authority Members Released </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1205174394 Paris AFP in English 1612 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1205174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, May 12 (AFP) -- The partial list of 
Palestinian authority members announced on Thursday [12 May] by 
chief PLO negotiator Nabil Sha'th is as follows: 
  - Yasir 'Arafat, PLO chairman 
  - Zakariya al-Agha, head of Arafat's mainstream Fatah 
faction in Gaza 
  - Frayh Abu-Midyan, former president of the Gaza Bar 
Association 
  - Faysal al-Husayni, the leading PLO man in the occupied 
territories 
  - Hanan 'Ashrawi, former spokeswoman of the negotiating 
team 
  - Sa'ib 'Urayqat, head of the Palestinian team to the 
bilateral talks 
  - Riyad al-Za'nun, head of the higher health council in 
the Gaza Strip 
  - Nabil Sha'th, PLO chief autonomy negotiator 
  - Yasir 'Amr, PLO executive committee member 
  - Intisar al-Wazir (Umm Jihad), widow of Arafat's 
second-in-command Khalil al-Wazir, who was killed in 1988 
  - 'Azmi al-Shu'aybi, head of the Palestinian Democratic 
Union in the occupied territories 
  - Ilyas Furayj, mayor of Bethlehem in the occupied West 
Bank 
  - 'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Haj Ahmad, a former deportee 
  - Ahmad Quray' (Abu-'Ala'), PLO economic departement chief 
  - Samir Ghawshah, Popular Struggle Front leader, PLO 
executive committee member 
  The authority is to take over on May 25, and 10 other 
members are to be announced. 

</TEXT>

