<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Urayqat: Committees To Manage Towns, Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Urayqat: Committees To Manage Towns, Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1305102394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 13 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1305102394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sa'ib 'Urayqat, who is a member of the Palestinian 
Autonomy Council, said that within a short time committees would 
be appointed to manage the Arab towns and villages inside the 
autonomous areas. These committees would make preparations to 
hold municipal elections within several months. 
  Sa'ib 'Urayqat confirmed to our correspondent Arye Gus that 
he had accepted the local government portfolio in the Autonomy 
Council. 'Urayqat, who is a Jericho resident, added that he was 
happy to see the Palestinian flag flying over the city. 
'Urayqat nevertheless noted that the Palestinians still had a 
long way to go and many challenges to face. 

</TEXT>

