<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat, IMF Delegation View Aid to Projects </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat, IMF Delegation View Aid to Projects </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205191294 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1205191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yasir 'Arafat, president of the state of Palestine 
and chairman of the PLO, today received IMF's delegation, headed 
by (Dr. George al-'Abid). 
  During the meeting, they discussed a number of important 
issues, most importantly IMF's aid to the present Palestinian 
authority and the agreed projects that would bolster Palestinian 
national authority and strengthen the implementation of the 
first phase of the peace plan. 
  They also discussed issues of common interest in the 
Palestinian self-rule territories. 
  The meeting was an opportunity to review the peace process 
and the means of making it a success. 

</TEXT>

