<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Rejects Conditions for Prisoner Release </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Rejects Conditions for Prisoner Release </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1205133094 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 12 May 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PM1205133094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Hamas Rejects Israeli Conditions for </F>
Releasing Its Prisoners"] 
  [Text] Damascus, AL-HAYAH -- The Islamic Resistance 
Movement (Hamas) has refused to respond to the conditions set by 
Israeli authorities for releasing its prisoners from Israelis 
jails. It stressed that linking their release with its support 
of the Oslo agreement is "a one-upmanship rejected by our 
mujahidin." 
  Ibrahim Ghawshah, official spokesman for Hamas, said that 
the 
movement "has decided not to accept the conditions set by 
Zionist occupation authorities for releasing our prisoners, 
namely to pledge not to return to what they termed the pledge to 
continue terrorist actions, and to support the capitulationist 
Gaza-Jericho agreement." Ghawshah added in a statement that 
"the detainees' release is a natural right which should not be 
linked to the required pledge. Because the resistance against 
the occupation is a legitimate right in all values and laws 
known to mankind. Thus it is not right to describe it as a 
terrorist action. Besides, the detainees cannot abandon a 
legitimate and national duty they are performing against the 
occupation." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

