<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   King Confers With Yemeni Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    King Confers With Yemeni Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1205164494 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 
12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1205164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the Royal Hashemite Court today, His Majesty 
King Husayn received Yemen's Foreign Minister Muhammad Salim 
Basindwah, who communicated a verbal message from President 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih. The message thanks his majesty for his 
attitude toward sisterly Yemen, and outlines the latest 
developments there. 
  His Majesty King Husayn told Basindwah that Jordan wants to 
see the Yemeni people stay united, within a single entity. 
Jordan is anxious for the gains achieved by the Yemeni people 
to be preserved. His majesty told the envoy the flow of Yemeni 
blood should be stemmed and outside intervention in the 
country's domestic affairs kept at bay. Jordan, his majesty 
added, is prepared to extend humanitarian aid to Yemen whenever 
the need arises. 
  The meeting was attended by Royal Court Chief al-Sharif Zayd 
Bin-Shakir; his majesty's adviser Khalid al-Karaki; Talal 
al-Hasan, minister of state for foreign affairs; and the Yemeni 
ambassador in Amman. 
  The Yemeni minister left Amman this afternoon and was seen 
off at the airport by Talal al-Hasan. 

</TEXT>

