<F P=102>   NC1205185794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1827 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1205185794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 12 May (MENA) -- The Egyptian Human Rights 
Organization [EHRO] issued a statement today dismissing a 
foreign news agency report attributed to an EHRO member that 
said the number of political detainees in Egypt is between 
20,000 and 30,000. 
  In its statement, EHRO said none of its officials had made 
such a statement during its news conference yesterday. EHRO 
stressed that the assertion that there are between 20,000 and 
30,000 detainees is not true. 

