<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Civil Administration To Pay Gaza Electricity Debt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Civil Administration To Pay Gaza Electricity Debt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1105134694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 11 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1105134694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It was decided at a discussion in the prime 
minister's bureau that the Civil Administration will pay the 
Gaza Strip's debt of approximately 37 million shekels to the 
Electricity Corporation. Israel will propose that, in the 
future, the Palestinians make monthly payments of approximately 
6-8 million shekels for their electricity consumption, and if 
they should be unable to pay, the sums will be deducted from 
other budgets earmarked for the autonomy. 
  In the wake of this decision, the Electricity Corporation 
has 
announced that it will not disconnect the power supply to the 
Gaza Strip as planned. This was reported by our correspondents 
Shlomo Raz and Shulamit Schmerling. Under the Israel-PLO 
agreement, the Gaza Strip is to receive electricity from Israel 
on an economic-commercial basis whose details will be finalized 
in negotiations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

