<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soldier, Truck Driver Shot, Wounded in Strip </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Soldier, Truck Driver Shot, Wounded in Strip </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1205111494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 12 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1205111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A soldier in an IDF [Israel Defense Forces] outpost 
in Jabalyah in the Gaza Strip was wounded in the knee by 
terrorists' gunfire. The soldier was taken to Soroka Hospital 
in Beersheba. Our Army affairs correspondent Karmela Menashe 
reports that several shots were fired at the outpost. The 
soldiers returned fire, and then another salvo was fired at 
them. A man suffering gunshot wounds was later found in 
al-Shifa' Hospital in Gaza, and the possibility that he may have 
been one of the terrorists is currently being examined. 
  A truck driver was wounded by gunfire near the settlement of 
Morag in the Qatif Bloc. He was moderately wounded and was 
evacuated to Soroka Hospital in Beersheba. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

