<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beilin Leaves for UK, To Discuss EU Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beilin Leaves for UK, To Discuss EU Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1205115294 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 12 May 94 p A11 </F>
<F P=103> TA1205115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by political correspondent Aluf Ben] </F>
  [Text] During recent negotiations on the new agreement 
between Israel and the European Union [EU], Israel has been 
encountering difficulties in its attempts to be accepted as an 
associate member to EU research and development plans. 
  According to reports from various European capitals which 
arrived in Jerusalem recently, the talks are being held up 
because Britain has been impeding the talks on approving 
Israel's acceptance to the research and development plans. 
  Deputy Foreign Minister Yosi Beilin is leaving this morning 
on a four-day visit to Britain, where he will hold discussions 
on promoting the Israel-EU relations and bilateral relations 
with Britain. 

</TEXT>

