<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Protest of `Fascists' in Italian Government Urged </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Protest of `Fascists' in Italian Government Urged </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1205113994 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT (24 SHA'OT 
supplement) in Hebrew 12 May 94 p 8 </F>

<F P=103> TA1205113994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT (24 SHA'OT 
supplement) </F>

<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Commentary by Sever Plotzker: "Do Not Let Fascism Have Its </F>
Way"] 
  [Excerpts] On 10 May, TV mogul Silvio Berlusconi, the 
newly elected Italian prime minister, presented the composition 
of his government: Berlusconi's popular movement -- which 
organized for the election at the record time of 10 weeks and 
swept most of the Italian voter's support -- is an alliance of 
three parties: Berlusconi's party, Forza Italia, a populist 
party seeking to turn Italy into a loose north-south federation; 
the Northern League; and the National Alliance, which contains 
the hardcore Italian neo- fascists. This is the first time 
fascists are members of a European government since 1944. 
[passage omitted] 
  Before it is too late -- before the representation of 
neo-fascists expands, before the new fascists are again accepted 
among the civilized European nations -- my government, the 
Government of Israel, the government of the state of the Jews, 
must take a demonstrative act against what is happening in Italy 
this spring of 1994. 
  We cannot just let this happen. I urge and expect Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin to express the Israeli Government's most 
determined protest over the fact that neo-fascists were made 
part of an Italian government. I expect Foreign Minister 
Shim'on Peres to recall Israel's ambassador in Rome for 
prolonged consultations. I strongly suggest that the membership 
of Italian observers in the Temporary International Presence in 
Hebron be suspended for as long as they are subject to a 
government the deputy prime minister of which is a neo-fascist. 
And, if all the above diplomatic hints do not help, I call on 
my government to downgrade the Israeli representation in Italy 
from the ambassadorial to the consular level, or even less. 
  I am aware of the fact that some Italians might view this as 
an interference with their domestic matters. Not true! 
Legitimizing fascism or neo-post-fascism is no domestic matter 
of any country. It is a virus that could spread like AIDS if it 
is not abolished at once. Even if the Italians are willing to 
stomach their fascists, we, the Jewish government, will scream 
and how. 
  It is not only that we are entitled to do so; it is our 
national duty. This is what the State of Israel is there for. 
We cannot afford to keep silent. We know the dreadful price of 
silence. There is no such thing as humanitarian fascism. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-59430 </DOCNO>
