<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-093 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid Holds News Conference, Comments on Salih </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bid Holds News Conference, Comments on Salih </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205112294 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0330 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1205112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice chairman of the 
Presidential Council and secretary general of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party [YSP], stressed the illegitimacy of A'li 
'Abdallah Salih as chairman of the Presidential Council, the 
illegitimacy of [words indistinct] in the Presidential Council, 
the illegitimacy of the speaker of the House of Representatives, 
and the illegitimacy of the Yemeni Reform Alliance group in the 
House of Representatives. 
  At a news conference in Aden yesterday evening, attended by 
representatives of local, Arab, and international press, brother 
'Ali Salim al-Bid explained that legitimacy and constitution 
complement each other. He said that the constitution specifies 
that the Presidential Council will consist of five elected 
members; the five members of the Council should then elect their 
chairman after they have taken the constitutional oath. 
However, that did not happen because al-Bid has not yet taken 
the oath. Therefore, the chairman has been illegally appointed 
and has not been elected by a complete council as the 
constitution specifies. 
  As for 'Abd al-Majid al-Zandani, his membership of the 
Presidential council is illegitimate because he took an oath 
contradictory to the oath specified by the Constitution. The 
same applies to the speaker of the House of Representatives and 
those members of the Yemeni Reform Alliance parliamentary group, 
who took an oath contradictory to the one specified by the 
Constitution. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid condemned the declaration of the 
state of emergency by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, whom he described as 
a dictator. Brother al-Bid pointed out that the Constitution 
specifies that a state of emergency may only be declared 
following a resolution by the National Defense Council, which 
met only once three years ago. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid added that all the resolutions 
adopted by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih are illegal because they were 
issued in the name of an illegitimate chairman. He said: 
Legitimacy today is the legitimacy of national unanimity, 
represented by the document of pledge and accord, and we take 
our legitimacy from our people, national unanimity, and the 
higher interests of the homeland and their balance in society. 
  He explained that there are many details which could be 
specified to emphasize the illegitimacy of many of the existing 
institutions. He said: We will soon present [word indistinct] 
our opinion of the legitimacy. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid said: We are approaching the 21st 
century, but there are those who refuse to recognize human 
rights, who try to limit civilian life, and who work toward 
consecrating armament, and pulling us back to the middle ages. 
That is why these people have rejected the course of the 
document of pledge and accord and have imposed this war on us, 
by which they direct strikes and stab at Yemen, its unity, 
people, and national [word indistinct]. 
  In his replies to questions from the correspondents about 
the 
military situation, brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid stressed that 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih and the forces of the Al al-Ahmar gang are 
deployed along the past division lines in order to renew the 
secession. He also emphasized that the al-Amaliqah units 
stationed in Abyan did not enter it during the war but were 
stationed in that governorate for four years, where they have 
their own camps. On the other hand, our units deployed in the 
Northern governorates were placed either in the same camps or 
neighboring ones. These camps were hit and destroyed. 
  He pointed out: When we approached unity we did not think of 
the military tactics of attacking it. We entered the union 
peacefully. Our aim is to construct our state in a peaceful and 
democratic way. We believed that the democratic forces and 
civilian life would influence and contain these military forces. 
However, in the end the military forces have disregarded 
everything, usurped freedom, opened detention camps, killed 
women and children, militarized the country, and spread terror 
and terrorism everywhere. This is the proof of their aggressive 
spirit and the inherited mentality of invasion in order to 
spread hegemony and [word indistinct]. 
  The brother secretary general of the Yemeni Socialist Party 
reiterated that the aggressive way chosen by the dictator 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih and his gang will not succeed. He pointed out 
that a new situation has been created among our people, and that 
many units led by the Al al-Ahmar gang have been forced to fight 
their brothers, shell the cities and villages, and to kill and 
shed the blood of the innocent. Therefore, they are working 
toward severing the ties of fraternity, friendship, and unity 
among the sons of the Yemeni people, and they are destroying the 
union with their actions, which stem from a mentality of 
invasion, occupation and looting. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid said: We have exhausted all the 
means of [words indistinct] and accepted all solutions, but 
unfortunately we are today forced to defend ourselves in a war 
which is imposed on us. We consider ourselves (?bound) by the 
document of pledge and accord [words indistinct] this document. 
  He stressed: We stand by all the honorable patriots and all 
the good-intentioned forces in order to build a democratic 
Yemen, as a country on whose basis we agreed unanimously in the 
document of pledge and accord. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid called on all the soldiers and 
officers, whom the dictator 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih throws in the 
fire of death, to resort to reason and patriotism and to abandon 
that unpatriotic and inhuman course. 
  He emphasized loudly: Rest assured that Aden will be 
impregnable to the invaders. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

