<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Information Minister on Options for `Secessionists' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Information Minister on Options for `Secessionists' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1305083594 Baghdad INA in Arabic 2005 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1305083594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Doha, 12 May (INA)--Information Minister Hasan 
al-Lawzi today said that the elements who ignited the military 
situation in the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] must leave the 
country or stand trial. 
  In a statement over the telephone to the QATARI NEWS AGENCY, 
al-Lawzi said that the opportunity is now open for the limited 
number of elements who ignited the situation to leave the 
country in order to spare the blood of the people and to stop 
destroying the country's resources. 
  He added that there is a chance for these elements, who are 
a 
minority in the YSP, to leave the country so that they will not 
cause any further losses in the southern governorates of Aden 
and Lahij. 
  He continued by saying: If they stay, these elements who are 
involved in the crime of engineering a secession and destroying 
the country must be interrogated and punished for violating the 
constitution and the law. 
  On Wednesday [11 May], President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih 
announced his willingness to give orders that would allow the 
secessionists to leave Yemen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

