<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reports on Battles, Casualties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on Battles, Casualties </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Former Border Areas Said Under Aden Control </H4>

<F P=102> EA1205171594 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1500 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1205171594 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Following a fierce battle in which the soldiers of 
the army of unity, democracy, and modernization emerged as 
heroes performing deeds of bravery unprecedented in our people's 
history, our forces succeeded in completely routing the foolish 
and [word indistinct] forces of the bloody al-Ahmar gang, 
forcing them to retreat to their rear positions in the direction 
of Qa'tabah. 
  Many members of the latter forces had earlier surrendered 
and 
joined the ranks of our forces, having been forced into the war 
by the al-Ahmar gang by various immoral means. Our forces are 
now in complete control of the entire areas of al-Dali' and 
Shu'ayb, having captured or put to flight the forces of the 
adventurist al-Ahmar gang. In the Bab al-Mandeb Kharaz area, 
our forces succeeded this morning in repulsing the offensive of 
the oppressive forces of the treacherous gang of the al-Ahmar 
clan, forcing them to retreat to their rear positions after 
driving them out of the Ra's al-Arah and the Kahabup center 
areas. Our forces are currently in control of this area, which 
is in the region of the former border existing before the union. 
  The Defense Ministry has expressed conviction that victory 
will soon be won and the destructive and oppressive war declared 
by the so-called 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih on 27 April 1994 will soon 
be silenced. 

</TEXT>

