<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   ARB'AT'ASHAR: `Stable Conditions' in Aden Region </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ARB'AT'ASHAR: `Stable Conditions' in Aden Region </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1205193594 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in English 
1600 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1205193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the press review] </F>
  [Text] The daily ARB'AT'ASHAR 14 OCTOBER newspaper 
continues to publish reports on the current developments and the 
war launched by the bloody al-Ahmar gang against the armed 
forces of the unity and democracy. It published reportages 
about the damages caused by the shelling of the residential 
apartments. 
  One of the reportages was written about the calm and 
tranquil 
situation in Dar Sa'd. It was compiled by a press and 
television team which came to Aden to cover the war events. The 
newspaper said in the reportages that one of the correspondents 
talked to the soldiers who were guarding the gates of al-Anad 
camp. The journalist described the stable conditions in this 
region thanks to the armed forces of the country and democracy 
which are controlling in the battlefield [sentence as heard]. 
  The journalist wondered about the lying information which 
falsifies the facts and confuses the people and [words 
indistinct]. He said: Such media deserve to be described as 
lying media, because it presents false information about the 
situation. He said: All information we have heard from the 
Sanaa media to the effect that 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih's forces had 
captured al-Dali' is untrue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

