<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sanaa: U.S. Embassy, EU Denounce Missile Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sanaa: U.S. Embassy, EU Denounce Missile Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1205142294 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1205142294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The U.S. Embassy in Sanaa today issued a statement 
on the current events in the country. The statement says: The 
Embassy of the United States of America strongly denounces and 
condemns any use of missiles and weapons of mass destruction in 
the current conflict, as this will result in civilian 
casualties. It calls for the cessation of the use of such 
weapons. The statement explains that the continued hostilities 
will lead to more civilian casualties on both sides. 
  The German Embassy, representing the European Unity [EU] 
chairmanship in Sanaa, issued an EU statement, saying: The 
ambassadors of EU member states to the Republic of Yemen deeply 
regret and denounce any use of missiles and illegitimate weapons 
in the ongoing conflict, as this will result in casualties among 
the civilians. They urge the immediate cessation of the use of 
such weapons. The statement explains that reliable reports 
have been received about civilian deaths and injuries as a 
result of the use of such weapons. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

