<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Judge Sa'id Mirza, who is investigating the 
assassination of former President Shaykh Bashir al-Jumayyil, has 
issued a warrant for the arrest of Habib al-Shartuni on murder 
charges following his escape from prison. 
  Philip Khayrallah, chairman of the Judicial Council, has set 
3 June as the date for the start of the trial of 'Abd-al-Hakim 
Hulayhil, Bilal Kafil, Hasan Mallat, Husayn Sahyun, and Murad 
Qaddur, who are charged with carrying out terrorist actions on 
the Dayr al-Balamand road with a view to fanning civil war, 
sectarian fighting, and sabotage on 22 June 1993. 

