<H3> <TI>   Arab Lawyers Demand Lifting of Sanctions on Iraq </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab Lawyers Demand Lifting of Sanctions on Iraq </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1405150894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1310 GMT 14 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1405150894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 14 May (MENA) -- The Arab Bar Association has 
expressed its concern about the continuation of the sanctions 
imposed on Iraq despite the fact that their harmful effects 
infringe on the Iraqi citizens' basic rights to food and 
medicine. 
  In a statement issued today, the association said that Arab 
lawyers, appalled by the continuation of these conditions 
imposed on the Iraqi people, appeal to the UN Security Council 
members and president, the UN secretary general, and 
international humanitarian organizations to immediately lift 
sanctions imposed on Iraq. 
  The statement was issued on the occasion of the debate that 
the UN Security Council will hold tomorrow to discuss continuing 
the sanctions on Iraq. 

