<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Cross Rafah Border Point En Route to Gaza </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Cross Rafah Border Point En Route to Gaza </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1505143294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1345 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1505143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rafah, 15 May (MENA) -- A new 314-strong Palestinian 
police force commanded by Colonel 'Abd-al-Majid Fadl Salih 
crossed at the Rafah border point on the way to Gaza today. 
  Col. Salih said the unit comes from the 'Ayn Jalut forces in 
Egypt together with some personnel from the forces stationed in 
Libya and Sudan. 
  Salih said the deployment of the Palestinian police forces 
continues in Gaza and Jericho. He said Badr forces have been 
deployed in Jericho and Rafah and that the northern, central, 
and southern sectors of the Gaza Strip have also been covered 
through deployment in Khan Yunus, Dayr al-Balah, Jabaliyh, and 
al- Shaja'iyah. It remains for the Palestinian force to deploy 
in Gaza City and the Eretz checkpoint on the border between 
Palestine and Israel, he said. 
  He said Palestinian police forces are now working to 
maintain 
security and order and protect vital installations, such as 
electricity and water stations, custom departments, ports, and 
airports. 
  Col. Salih praised the facilities provided by Egypt and the 
efforts made by the Egyptian Administration at the Customs 
Office, Passport Department, and border security to organize the 
entry of Palestinian forces. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

