<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Ashrawi Declines National Authority Post </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Ashrawi Declines National Authority Post </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1405180994 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 14 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1405180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Basil Abu-Sumayah from the occupied territories] </F>
  [Excerpt] U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher will 
be the first Western official at the foreign minister level to 
visit the Palestinian self-rule area in Jericho. Christopher is 
scheduled to arrive in the city on Tuesday [17 May] to meet, in 
the headquarters of the Palestinian National Security Forces, 
with the commander of these forces, Brigadier Hajj Isma'il; 
senior Palestinian officers; and leading Palestinian figures, 
including Dr. Sa'ib 'Urayqat, a member of the Palestinian 
authority. The U.S. secretary will also meet with Palestinian 
figures in East Jerusalem. 
  In a related development, Dr. Hanan 'Ashrawi, former 
spokeswoman of the Palestinian delegation has stressed that she 
will not participate in the Palestinian authority that is 
charged with the running of the Gaza sector and the Jericho 
area. She told our radio that she will give priority to the 
Independent Palestinian Commission for Citizens Rights. 
'Ashrawi is the secretary general of that commission. 
  'Ashrawi urged Palestinians, including the opposition, to 
join in building Palestinian society, both in the national 
authority, the administrative agencies, and the institutions. 
She said members of the authority must have competence and 
credibility and be able to show commitment and will power so 
they can win the approval of all segments of Palestinian 
society. She said: There must be an integrated plan for 
reconstitution with the participation of all. No one can escape 
their responsibilities and the future challenges. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

