<H4>    Returns to Beirut </H4>

<F P=102> NC1405184394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1800 GMT 14 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1405184394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri returned to Beirut 
from Damascus at 2030 today after holding more than three hours 
of talks with Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad. 
  Before his departure from Damascus, Prime Minister al-Hariri 
said: It is natural for us to visit President al-Asad at every 
phase of our deadlines and to consult with him on matters of 
interest to the two brotherly countries. He added: Syria takes 
great credit for Lebanon's stability, a credit that is 
recognized by every Lebanese who is interested in national 
detente. 
  Al-Hariri added: My meeting with President al-Asad today was 
to assert these feelings and to thank him for his initiatives 
for Lebanon. It was also an opportunity to review the march 
toward stability in Lebanon and to coordinate the two countries' 
stances on the peace process. 

</TEXT>

