<H4>    Al-Dali' Reportedly `Purged' </H4>

<F P=102> JN1305170394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1600 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1305170394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Yemeni News Agency correspondent in the al-Dali' 
district has reported the return of normal life to the city of 
al-Dali' and neighboring areas after the forces of 
constitutional legitimacy purged them of the forces misled by 
the secessionist elements in the Socialist Party. The 
correspondent said citizens resumed work and shops opened 
normally. 
  In another development, the [Yemeni Television] First 
Channel 
team shot pictures of the 'Abbud Camp area and other areas which 
were brought under the control of the constitutional legitimacy 
forces, including arms depots, tanks, and vehicles left behind 
by the fleeing forces misled by the elements of apostasy, 
rebellion, and secession. The news team interviewed citizens 
and fighters who joined the legitimacy forces. They expressed 
their pleasure that the forces of unity and legitimacy had 
managed to rid the area and its citizens of the hegemony of the 
forces of apostasy, rebellion, and secession and their divisive 
practices. 
  The brother citizens in the city of al-Dali' and neighboring 
areas appreciated the good treatment extended to them by the 
forces of legitimacy and unity, contrary to the falsehoods 
propagated by the secessionist elements in the Socialist Party. 
This good treatment proved that words are coupled by deeds by 
the legitimate leadership under brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Presidential Council and 
supreme commander of the Armed Forces, who instructed the Armed 
Forces to extend all possible assistance to the citizens in the 
region and protect their property in confirmation of the 
responsibility shouldered by the state of unity under his 
leadership for the sake of protecting the citizens throughout 
Yemen. 

</TEXT>

