<DATE1>  14 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of 13-16 May Clashes in North, South </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of 13-16 May Clashes in North, South </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Commander Prepared To Capture Aden </H4>

<F P=102> NC1405205694 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 2000 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1405205694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Field Colonel 'Ali al-Jayfi, commander of the 
northern Yemeni al-'Amaliqah Brigade, has said that his troops, 
backed with tanks and artillery units, are currently stationed 
at a distance of 40 km northeast of Aden, having inflicted 
successive defeats on the southern forces and overrun their 
strongholds in Abyan. 
  Speaking to an international media delegation touring the 
areas of the fighting, Col. al-Jayfi said that some northern 
troops have arrived at the al-'Alam area 20 km north of Aden. 
He pointed out that President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih ordered the 
siege tightened on Aden, stronghold of the Yemeni Socialist 
Party. The northern commander added that his troops are 
repositioning themselves around the city and waiting for a 
political decision to capture it. 
  An official military source in Sanaa has said that the 
northern troops advanced in the al-Dali' sector and regained 
control of the southern al-Musaymir town. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

