<H4>    Commander: Troops 15-20 km From Aden </H4>

<F P=102> JN1505090094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0740 GMT 15 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1505090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by al-'Amaliqah Forces' Commander Colonel 'Ali </F>
al-Ja'ithi; place and date not given--recorded] 
  [Text] From this area in the Abyan Governorate and from 
the al-'Amaliqah camp in the town of Zinjibar, I am happy to 
reassure our people and all our colleagues and brothers in the 
Armed Forces that the situation in the Abyan Governorate is 
stable and that our Armed Forces are completely in control of 
the governorate and that the Armed Forces units and al-'Amaliqah 
men are on the outskirts of Aden, only 15 to 20 km from Aden. 
The fighting is continuing with a great momentum and with high 
morale. What is rumored by the media of the secessionists, 
liars, and charlatans, the advocates of apostasy and secession, 
is baseless. Their units have been liquidated, whether in 
Abyan, the 20th Brigade, the Madram Brigade, or the [YSP] 
militia and party units here, as well as all of the units they 
sent to Abyan such as the 30th Brigade, the Unity Brigade 
dispatched from Hadhramaut, and the 5th Brigade that arrived 
from Aden. These units were confronted with firmness, faith, 
and with high morale and a great number of them were destroyed. 
  The enemy is being utterly defeated. Its defeat has been 
reflected in its psychology. It has now started to hit cities 
and civilians with missiles and artillery. We have avoided 
fighting in cities because we regard ourselves as protectors of 
people and citizens. We have avoided that in order to preserve 
citizen's lives and property. But the defeated and the confused 
ones choose civilians as their victims. 

</TEXT>

