<H3> <TI>   Arab League Delegation Visits Northern Region </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab League Delegation Visits Northern Region </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Inspects Sanaa Missile Impact Site </H4>

<F P=102> JN1405175694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1405175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A visiting Arab League delegation, led by Major 
General Muhammad Sa'id Bayraqdar, the Arab League assistant 
secretary general for military affairs, this afternoon visited 
the site where a missile exploded. The missile was fired by the 
secessionist, rebellious gang of the Socialist Party last 
Tuesday [10 May] on a densely populated quarter of the capital, 
Sanaa. 
  The Arab League delegation saw the destruction caused by the 
missile's explosion over the citizens' homes which fell over the 
heads of their residents. They also saw the damage caused to 
many neighboring houses. 
  The delegation listened to citizens on the material and 
human 
losses sustained in the explosion, which claimed the lives of 23 
martyrs and left dozens others injured. This is in addition to 
the panic caused for women, children, and old people who were 
asleep the moment the missile of the secessionists exploded in 
the capital of the unity state, targeting the lives of secure 
civilians. 

</TEXT>

