<H3> <TI>   Arab League Delegation Visits Northern Region </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab League Delegation Visits Northern Region </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Received by Presidential Council Member </H4>

<F P=102> JN1405183394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1405183394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Abd-al-'Aziz 'Abd-al-Ghani, member of the 
Presidential Council, has received the Arab League delegation 
led by brother Major General Muhammad Sa'id Bayraqdar, assistant 
secretary general for military affairs. The Arab League 
delegation is currently on a visit to our country. 
  The member of the Presidential Council received a message 
addressed to brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council, from Arab League Secretary 
General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid on the current developments in 
our country. The message expresses the Arab League's concern to 
maintain Yemeni unity as a Yemeni national gain and a pan-Arab 
achievement from which there must be no retreat. 
  Brother 'Abd-al-'Aziz 'Abd-al-Ghani affirmed to the Arab 
League delegation that the rebellious faction in the [Yemeni] 
Socialist Party [YSP], which provoked the military situation, 
despite the exhausting efforts and many concessions made to the 
YSP to avoid military confrontation. However, the misguided 
faction continued with its stubbornness and dragged the country 
into the current situation. He stressed that the Yemeni 
leadership is keen to end the fighting by adhering to 
Constitutional legitimacy and its Constitutional and executive 
institutions as well as by sticking to the results of the 
parliamentary elections held on 27 April 1993. 
  The member of the Presidential Council also expressed our 
country's appreciation of the Arab League's concern about what 
is happening in our country, for which the rebellious factions 
in the YSP leadership are held responsible. He added that 
Yemeni unity represents a great gain for our Yemeni people, who 
will defend and protect themselves from any plotting concocted 
by the rebellious faction in the YSP leadership, whose grudge 
against our people and their people made them shell the capital, 
Sanaa, and other Yemeni cities with Scud missiles. He said: 
The determination of our people to defend unity and democracy 
cannot be shaken by these desperate criminal attempts. 

</TEXT>

