  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister 'Abd-al-Wahhab al-Anisi 
yesterday received an Arab League delegation led by Major 
General Muhammad Sa'id Bayraqdar, assistant secretary general 
for military affairs. The Arab League delegation is currently on 
a visit to our country. 
  The two sides reviewed the developments in our country in 
light of the war ignited in the homeland by the gang of apostasy 
and secession in the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] leadership. 
  The deputy prime minister explained the developments in the 
Yemeni arena, holding the secessionist rebellious leadership of 
the YSP responsible for igniting the military situation in the 
country. He noted that this took place in accordance with a 
premeditated scheme and began with the actions of this gang, 
which is rebelling against political legitimacy by violating the 
framework of the government coalition, paralyzing the legitimate 
institutions, casting doubts about them, and obstructing their 
role. 
  The deputy prime minister expressed his appreciation for the 
Arab League's role in shouldering its pan-Arab responsibility to 
protect Yemeni unity, which is considered a pan-Arab achievement 
that concerns all the sons of the Arab nation, and to support 
justice and constitutional legitimacy. 

</TEXT>

