<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden Council Calls For Arab League Intervention </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1405132294 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2045 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1405132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Council of Coordination Between Parties and the 
Masses, Organizations, and Nationalist Citizens in Aden 
Governorate has sent a telegram to brother Dr. 'Ismat 
'Abd-al-Majid, secretary general of the Arab League. The 
telegram calls on the secretary general and the Arab member 
states to intervene, directly, effectively, and quickly in order 
to halt the fighting between the Yemeni military forces and 
secure towns and citizens from any acts of aggression. Also, it 
asks the League to pave the way for the political forces to hold 
dialogues about the implementation of the document of pledge and 
accord, considering that that document is the sole solution, and 
to seek a new formula for unity. 
  The telegram said it was necessary for the Council of 
Coordination to address this direct call to the secretary 
general of the Arab League at a time when Yemeni weapons were 
being pointed at other Yemenis and when Yemen was being 
destroyed and its people exterminated after the achievement of 
unity. 

</TEXT>

