<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oil Minister: Production Unaffected by Clashes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oil Minister: Production Unaffected by Clashes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1305201794 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1800 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1305201794 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Salih Abu-Bakr Bin-Husaynun, the minister 
of oil and mineral resources, has confirmed that Yemeni oil 
production and (?refining) operations have not been affected, in 
spite of the violent fighting going on in our country. Brother 
Bin-Husaynun, who is currently visiting a number of Arab 
capitals, said that the production of oil from the Ma'rib, 
Shabwah, and Hadramawt fields was proceeding normally, and that 
the oil installations have not been subjected to any attacks. 
He pointed out that defense precautions had been taken to 
prevent sabotage operations and repulse any attacks. 
  He said that oil was a resource belonging to all the Yemeni 
people. The forces of the bloody al-Ahmar gang should avoid any 
attacks on these installations. 

</TEXT>

