<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gunmen Kill Soldiers, Policeman in Asyut </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gunmen Kill Soldiers, Policeman in Asyut </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Minister Says Situation Under Control </H4>

<F P=102> NC1505143894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1340 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1505143894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 5 May (MENA) -- Interior Minister Hasan 
al-Alfi has affirmed that security forces have succeeded in 
controlling the situation in the Governorate of Asyut in Upper 
Egypt. They have struck at the terrorist dens and captured the 
fugitive terrorists. 
  Al-Alfi said during his meeting today with a number of 
public 
security commanders and officers who have been transferred to 
work in the field of criminal investigations and political 
security in the governorate that the Interior Ministry is 
currently developing weapons and equipment and is providing 
training. 
  He clarified that the ministry is rebuilding its structures 
in the geographic regions of Upper Egypt. He noted that the 
ministry's current policy is to strengthen the confidence 
between the people and their executive leaders to isolate the 
outlaws and confront them. 
  During the meeting, the minister explained the current 
security policy. He also spoke about the mistakes they 
committed in the past, how they dealt with them in the security 
field, and how they learned about these mistakes. 

</TEXT>

