<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Talks With PLO Conclude in Amman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Economic Talks With PLO Conclude in Amman </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Closing Session Postponed </H4>

<F P=102> JN1305150094 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1100 GMT 
13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1305150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The closing session of the Jordanian-Palestinian 
Economic Committee, due to have convened in Amman this morning, 
has been postponed. Also postponed was a subsequent news 
conference by the chairmen of the Jordanian and Palestinian 
sides to the committee, Dr. Jawad al-'Anani, minister of state 
for cabinet affairs and minister of information; and Mr. Ahmad 
Quray', the PLO's Economic Department chief. 
  In a statement to the JORDANIAN NEWS AGENCY, Dr. al-'Anani 
attributed the delay to the preoccupation of the Palestinian 
leadership with numerous issues, including the formation of the 
Palestinian Authority Council and matters related to the 
transfer of power. 
  The final session of the Jordanian-Palestinian talks that 
began in Amman Tuesday [10 May] is due to be held within days. 
  During the two-day meeting, the committee addressed numerous 
economic items, including trade, banking, monetary policies, 
customs, and tourism. 

</TEXT>

