<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-59563 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes094_m_94009" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-094 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  14 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Senate Bosnian Arms Resolution Welcomed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Senate Bosnian Arms Resolution Welcomed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1405173094 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1600 GMT 
14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1405173094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Senate has expressed appreciation for the U.S. 
Senate's call for the lifting of the unjust arms embargo on the 
people of Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  In a cable in the name of the Senate to the president of the 
U.S. Senate, Senate President Ahmad al-Lawzi expressed hope that 
this step will be followed by other steps until the embargo is 
lifted and this peace-loving nation can acquire the means for 
legitimate self-defense and the liberation of their national 
soil, against an all-out war of annihilation in which atrocities 
are committed under the gaze of the civilized world. 
  Al-Lawzi stressed that if the United States plays its 
leading 
role in deterring aggression and preventing it from making any 
regional gains, it will restore confidence in the world order 
and international law and the UN Charter. This will spare the 
world and future generations wars and disasters motivated by 
racial and religious bias and the oppression of the weak by the 
strong. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

