<H3> <TI>   Reaction Continues to Alleged Embassy Bugging </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reaction Continues to Alleged Embassy Bugging </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ayatollah Condemns UK Government </H4>

<F P=102> LD1305120394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1305120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In today's Tehran Friday prayers, Ayatollah 
Emami-Kashani condemned the British Government for installing a 
bugging device in the Iranian Embassy in London. 
  The interim Friday prayers leader of Tehran referred to 
Britain's record in espionage activities and said: This recent 
espionage activity in London against the Islamic Republic of 
Iran demonstrates the continuation of plots hatched by arrogant 
countries against the Islamic revolution; but such conspiracies 
are, as ever, doomed to fail, thanks to the vigilance and 
alertness of the Muslim people of Iran. 
  On the great hajj congregation, he said: The gathering of a 
cross-section of one billion world Muslims at pilgrimage is a 
suitable opportunity to review various political, social, and 
economic problems of the world of Islam and their solutions so 
that, upon their return to their countries, Muslims could 
implement those solutions. 
  He said the designation of a day for the support of Bosnian 
Muslims by the eminent leader's representative office was a 
correct use of the hajj to draw the attention of Muslims to 
problems of the world of Islam. 
  Ayatollah Emami-Kashani praised the people for participating 
in the international book exhibition and said: That matter shows 
that the people of Iran care about cultural issues. 

</TEXT>

