<H3> <TI>   Reaction Continues to Alleged Embassy Bugging </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reaction Continues to Alleged Embassy Bugging </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    More Embassies Suspect Bugging </H4>

<F P=102> LD1305134694 Tehran IRNA in English 1251 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1305134694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] London, May 13, IRNA -- Following the disclosure of 
the British Government's bugging of the Iranian Embassy here, 
other ambassadors in London are skeptical of the security of 
their embassy vis-a-vis the government's espionage activities. 
  An Asian diplomat here has told his Iranian counterpart that 
there is a high likelihood that the British intelligence has 
carried out similar activities regarding the other embassies. 
  "We intend to carry out a thorough search in our embassy for 
sure," he said. 
  He noted that embassies of the Islamic countries are more 
exposed to the British eavesdropping due to the London's concern 
over the increasing growth of Islamism in Britain. 
  "Even the ambassadors of the European countries who are 
concerned over the issue, sarcastically ask the British 
politicians in their meetings as in what part of their embassies 
the British Government installed its eavsedropping devices," 
said the diplomat. 

</TEXT>

