<H3> <TI>   Committee To Work With Zagreb on Bosnia Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Committee To Work With Zagreb on Bosnia Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1405102794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1405102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Imam Khomeyni Relief Committee and the Zagreb 
Merhamet [Charity] Foundation will be cooperating in giving aid 
to Muslims in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  In a meeting with the Imam Khomeyni Relief Committee, the 
head and other officials of the Merhamet Foundation, praising 
the Islamic Republic of Iran's extensive assistance given to the 
people of Bosnia, called for cooperation in the fields of 
agriculture, livestock rearing, and setting up of carpet-weaving 
workshops for women in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  The Imam Khomeyni Relief Committee supervisor declared 
readiness for all-round assistance for Bosnian Muslims and the 
exchange of experiences gained in relief work done for the 
deprived in that country. 

</TEXT>

