<H3> <TI>   'Aziz Meets Vorontsov, Ekeus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Aziz Meets Vorontsov, Ekeus </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1405103494 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0940 GMT 14 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1405103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New York, 14 May (INA)--At his place of residence 
here last night, Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 'Aziz met with 
Russian Ambassador to the UN Yuliy Vorontsov. 
  The deputy prime minister also met with Henrick Fally [name 
as transliterated], Brazilian deputy permanent representative, 
whose country is a nonpermanent member of the UN Security 
Council. 
  Tariq 'Aziz also met yesterday with British Ambassador David 
Hannay, Djbouti Ambassador Roble Olhay, and Ambassador Rolf 
Ekeus, chairman of the UN Security Council Special Commission. 
  Following his one-hour meeting with Tariq 'Aziz, Amb. Ekeus 
told reporters that the meeting was fruitful and that there was 
a common understanding between the two sides. 
  He explained that the two sides discussed developments in 
all 
fields, as well as monitoring and future verification. 

</TEXT>

