<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Regime Reportedly Uses Napalm in Attack on North </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Regime Reportedly Uses Napalm in Attack on North </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1505165494 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 15 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1505165494 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 15 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Kurdistan office of the Supreme Assembly of the 
Islamic Revolution in Iraq [SAIRI] has stated that an armored 
brigade of the Iraqi regime has launched a major offensive 
against a number of villages in the Dhi Qar Governorate. 
  A statement issued by the office said that the regime's 
artillery bombarded [words indistinct]. SAIRI sources said that 
the regime used napalm bombs in the attack. 

</TEXT>

