<H3> <TI>   U.S. Secretary of State, Delegation Arrive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Secretary of State, Delegation Arrive </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Al-Asad Receives Christopher </H4>

<F P=102> JN1605052994 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 0415 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1605052994 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Hafiz al-Asad received U.S. Secretary of 
State Warren Christopher yesterday evening. 
  The meeting was attended by Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' 
and Dennis Ross, the U.S. coordinator for the Middle East peace 
process. 
  The attendees discussed the Middle East peace process. 
President al-Asad listened to what Christopher conveyed and 
presented Syria's viewpoint on the peace process and its 
objectives. 
  It was agreed to resume the talks when Christopher returns 
to 
Damascus. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

