<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemen's Basindwah Conveys Salih's Message, Departs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemen's Basindwah Conveys Salih's Message, Departs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1305155294 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1305155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Hafiz al-Asad received Yemeni Foreign 
Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah at al-Rawdah Palace at 1230 
today. Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' attended the audience. 
Basindwah conveyed to the president a message from President 
'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Yemeni Presidential 
Council. Talks dealt with Yemeni developments. 
  The president voiced Syria's concern over the bloody events 
in fraternal Yemen and renewed Syria's appeal for the Yemeni 
brothers to renounce fighting and resort to resolving 
differences by brotherly dialogue, out of concern for Yemeni 
unity and the safety and security of the Yemeni people. 
  The Yemeni foreign minister left Damascus at 1630 today. He 
was seen off at Damascus International Airport by Foreign 
Minister Faruq al-Shar', a number of Foreign Ministry officials, 
and the Yemeni embassy staff in Damascus. 
  In a statement to the SANA correspondent, Basindwah said: 
The 
aim of my visit to Damascus was to convey a message from 
President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih to his brother President Hafiz 
al-Asad. Today I was honored to meet with the president. I 
conveyed the message and briefed him on the latest Yemeni 
developments. I found the president fully understanding and 
concerned about Yemeni security and independence. Basindwah 
added: I found President Hafiz al-Asad extremely concerned about 
Yemeni unity. No wonder, President Hafiz al-Asad is one of the 
pioneers of Arab unity. Yemeni unity is a national achievement 
and a pan-Arab gain. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

