<HT>    "drnes094_o_94010" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-094 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  15 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arab League Chief Arrives for Coordination Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab League Chief Arrives for Coordination Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Comments on Yemen Crisis </H4>

<F P=102> NC1505093494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0905 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1505093494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 15 May (MENA)--Arab League Secretary 
General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid has stated that the League has 
proposed a peaceful overture for resolving the Yemeni crisis and 
halting the continuing deterioration in the situation there. 
Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid, who is currently visiting Syria, said that 
the message he sent to Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih 
yesterday constitutes an initiative and contains elements that 
would guarantee an end to the crisis. 
  In a statement to a MENA correspondent in Damascus, Dr. 
'Abd-al-Majid said that the first thing that must be done is end 
the fighting between the brothers there, noting that the Arab 
League is holding intensive consultations and contacts with a 
number of Yemeni leaders on holding a national dialogue instead 
of continuing the internecine fighting. He refused to disclose 
the details of the initiative now, noting that replying to the 
initiative is now in the hands of the Yemeni leaders themselves. 
He stressed that the Arab League is eager to see the delegation 
now in Yemen succeed in its mission. The League, he said, has 
decided to consider its mission in Yemen to be open-ended. In 
the meantime, Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid today received a lengthy report 
on the situation and developments in Yemen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

