  [Text] Sanandaj (Kurdistan Prov.), May 12, IRNA -- The 
situation in the northeastern Iraqi city of Sulaimaniya is 
chaotic, sources close to the Islamic Movement of Iraqi 
Kurdistan reported here today. 
  They added that sporadic clashes continue in northern Iraq 
among the Kurdish groups. 
  They said that on Wednesday at Dyana and Rawndouz the 
Kurdish 
Hizbullah revolutionary forces led by Sheikh Adham Barzani have 
regained control of Ziweh and Barziweh from the Patriotic Union 
of Kurdistan (PUK). 
  The Islamic Movement of Iraqi Kurdistan said its forces 
attacked Khormal, Rouzeh Biareh and Towaila in response to 
recent aggressions of the Jalal Talebani led PUK. 
  The reports have yet to be confirmed by independent sources. 

