<H3> <TI>   Chairman of Arab-Islamic Rally Party Murdered </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chairman of Arab-Islamic Rally Party Murdered </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Lawyer's Death Follows Abduction </H4>

<F P=102> NC1505105394 Paris AFP in English 0934 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1505105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Algiers, May 15 (AFP) -- The chairman of the 
Arab-Islamic Rally party has been murdered after being abducted, 
press reports said here Sunday [15 May]. 
  Laid Grine, 49, who was also an Algiers lawyer, was found 
Saturday morning near Algiers with his throat cut, the reports 
said. 
  The lawyer had been captured the previous day by 
unidentified 
abductors from his house at Bordj El Mokhfi east of Algiers. 
  There has been no official response to his kidnapping and 
murder, but press reports said he had succeeded Wednesday in 
gaining the acquittal of an Islamic fundamentalist being tried 
by one of the country's special "anti-terrorism" courts. 

</TEXT>

