<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sifi Visits Police Station, Comments on Stability </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sifi Visits Police Station, Comments on Stability </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605205694 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1605205694 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Prime Minister Mokdad Sifi paid 
an unexpected visit to the police station of El Anasser, where 
he was briefed by the station chief on the difficult conditions 
in which policemen carry out their mission to guarantee the 
public's safety. 
  [Begin Sifi recording] We will look into the means 
available. 
God willing, we will make an effort to provide you with the 
means in all fields. We will have to be realistic and bear in 
mind the circumstances and the means available to the state. 
We, as a government, and also the people notice that the 
policemen are sacrificing their lives to defend this homeland so 
that it can remain a state of law. The main thing is that this 
is a noble mission that concerns the defense of one of the basic 
human rights. Many people talk about human rights but we should 
not forget that the main and the most crucial human right is the 
right to life, and the defense of this right is a noble mission. 
  This mission is carried out by the police and all security 
corps who have sacrificed so much for the state and for Algeria. 
Algeria will not forget these sacrifices, which aim to protect 
the citizens and their property and defend this nation and this 
people. I must say and stress that the state, with Mr. Liamine 
Zeroual at its head, is opposing this violence and will continue 
to do so until the situation quiets down and things return to 
normal and until stability is restored, God willing. This will 
be relentless until stability and tranquillity are restored so 
that we can let our people choose their representatives. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

