<H3> <TI>   Holiday Postpones Cairo Talks; No New Date Set </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Holiday Postpones Cairo Talks; No New Date Set </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1605115294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1124 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1605115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cairo, 16 May (MENA) -- MENA has learned that the 
Palestinian-Israeli negotiations scheduled to be held in Cairo 
tomorrow, Tuesday, have been postponed until after the 'Id 
al-Adha holiday. 
  Diplomatic sources in Cairo said the talks were postponed 
because of the Muslims' celebration of 'Id al-Adha next week, 
which precludes continuing the talks. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

