<H3> <TI>   `Arafat Remarks on Jihad, Jerusalem Draw Reaction </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Arafat Remarks on Jihad, Jerusalem Draw Reaction </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Council Member `Astonished' at Remarks </H4>

<F P=102> TA1805074894 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0500 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1805074894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone interview with Dr. Zakariya al-Agha, member of </F>
the National Authority, by Itay Engel; place not given -- live, 
in English] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] [Engel] Dr. al-Agha, can we 
ask you to relate to the statement of Chairman 'Arafat in 
Johannesburg? The person who is in charge of the Palestinian 
side in this peace agreement talks about the need for the 
continuation of the jihad against the State of Israel. 
  [Al-Agha] I think when we started this peace process, we 
started the negotiations. Indeed, I am astonished about what is 
said in the broadcast about this, and indeed I didn't hear this 
statement. I have no official thought about this, so I would 
have to ask my chairman to understand what happened about this. 
  [Engel] I see. And if he says to you that indeed, he said 
and talked about the idea of the jihad, so you are going to 
implement now the idea of jihad, or you are going to continue 
with the peace process? 
  [Al-Agha] No, no, maybe the head means not only the armed 
struggle, but also any other means, like negotiations, like 
other. I don't think -- I am sure that Mr. 'Arafat doesn't mean 
what happened. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

