<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qaddumi Said To Assail Agreement in Fatah Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qaddumi Said To Assail Agreement in Fatah Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1705183994 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1705183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis--Informed Palestinian sources say that the 
Fatah Revolutionary Council led by Yasir 'Arafat yesterday heard 
a report by Faruq Qaddumi, the Fatah secretary general, in which 
he attacked the recent Cairo agreement between Israel and the 
PLO. The sources say that Qaddumi's attack was particularly 
directed at 'Arafat's agreement to concede the right of 
representation for the national authority abroad. The sources 
said that a number of the Fatah Movement's Central Committee 
members are unwilling to leave for Jericho and assume their 
duties within the so-called national authority. The source said 
that Faruq Qaddumi, Hani al-Hasan, Khalid al-Hasan, Muhammad 
Jihad, and Muhammad Ghunaym have refused to go to Jericho, 
especially since there are differences on coordinating work 
between the Fatah commands at home and abroad. 

</TEXT>

