<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman: `Zionist' Attacks Not To Go Unpunished </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman: `Zionist' Attacks Not To Go Unpunished </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1705182294 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio in 
Arabic 1630 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1705182294 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Following the crime perpetrated by Zionist settlers 
in Hebron yesterday, an official spokesman for the Palestine 
National Liberation Movement, Fatah, [dissident] has stated that 
what happened in Hebron yesterday was definite proof exposing 
the falsehoods that have been going on for some time, concerning 
the agreements that Yasir 'Arafat concluded with the Zionist 
enemy. 
  The spokesman added that what happened in Hebron yesterday 
also confirmed the extent of both 'Arafat's involvement and his 
standing in the Zionist enemy's trench. He asserted that our 
militant people will continue their intifadah and daily struggle 
and will not pay attention to the falsehoods and deception 
pursued by the 'Arafatist group regarding its agreements with 
the enemy. The Zionist attacks and massacres will not go 
unpunished, he said. 

</TEXT>

