<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fatah Member on Future Planning in Gaza, Jericho </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah Member on Future Planning in Gaza, Jericho </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1605153894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1350 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1605153894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 16 May (MENA) -- 'Abbas Zaki, Fatah Central 
Committee member, stated that the committee met with PLO Fatah 
leader and PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat last night. The committee 
discussed completing the formation of the Palestinian National 
Authority Council and building the authority's institutions in 
Gaza and Jericho. 
  In a statement to MENA in Tunis, Zaki said the committee 
also 
discussed Fatah's future strategy, because Fatah's role has not 
yet ended and because it is responsible for transforming the new 
Palestinian entity in Gaza and Jericho into a Palestinian state. 
  In his statement, the Palestinian official said that the 
committee assessed Fatah's future political and practical 
policies and the transfer of 1,200 PLO cadres from Tunis to Gaza 
and Jericho during the next stage. 
  Reacting to reports about his appointment as the Palestine 
ambassador to Oman, Zaki said that as a member of the Fatah 
Movement he is committed to the instructions of the Fatah 
leadership, whether inside or outside the territories. 

</TEXT>

