  [Text] Jibril al-Rujub and Muhammad Dahlan, who will be 
in charge of internal security in the West Bank and the Gaza 
Strip on behalf of the PLO, will arrive in the autonomous area 
on Tuesday [17 May]. Jibril al-Rujub told our correspondent 
Karmela Menashe he will arrive to the Allenby Bridge with 
several of his aides Tuesday morning, from where he will 
continue to Hebron. Al-Rujub expressed satisfaction with the 
rate of IDF [Israel Defense Forces] withdrawal from the autonomy 
areas. He said it feels very good to return after six years and 
five months in the diaspora, and 17 years in prison. Al-Rujub 
says the two nations have no alternative to coexistence. He 
defined this a national and religious duty. 

