<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Large Number' of Detainees To Be Released </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Large Number' of Detainees To Be Released </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1605170594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1520 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1605170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 16 May (MENA) -- Interior Minister Hasan 
al-Alfi has ordered the release of a large number of detainees 
who, according to the State Security Intelligence services, have 
renounced extremism, departure from the right religion, and 
terrorist practices. 
  The Interior Ministry issued a statement saying these 
releases demonstrate that various police agencies are fully 
aware of movements of terrorist groups at home and abroad. It 
also proves that these agencies firmly adhere to law and 
legitimacy, honestly shoulder their national responsibility, and 
highly appreciate the public's support for them in their 
decisive confrontation with bloody terrorism and its elements, 
which target the nation and its interests. 
  An official security source at the Interior Ministry 
stressed 
that the release reflects a firm and credible policy by the 
Ministry regarding the emergency law; namely, that it should not 
be applied except against the elements that pose a threat to 
society. 
  The source said that these release orders will be 
implemented 
within hours, and will be followed by releases of other 
detainees whose files and positions on terrorism and extremism 
are now being reviewed by the State Security Intelligence 
agencies. 

</TEXT>

