BFN 

  [Text] The third conference on Ahl al-Bayt -- peace be upon 
them -- was held today at the esteemed leader's headquarters in 
holy Mecca. Our correspondent in Mecca sent the following 
report: 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Dear listeners of the midday 
news bulletin of the Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
[IRI], I am speaking to you from the esteemed leader's 
headquarters in holy Mecca. The third Ahl al-Bayt conference 
was held here today, attended by a group of cultural, 
scientific, and religious personalities from Iran and other 
Islamic countries. Various speakers from the IRI, Iraq, 
Afghanistan, Nigeria, Turkey, Azerbaijan and the United States 
addressed the audience on the social circumstances of the Ahl 
al-Bayt followers throughout the world, and their struggle 
against tyranny and dictatorship. 
  Despite the restrictions imposed by the Saudi police, the 
esteemed leader's headquarters is witnessing a constant flow of 
Iranian and non-Iranian pilgrims, and the ceremonies held inside 
the headquarters are warmly welcomed. 

</TEXT>

