Daily Report 
<DATE1>  16 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARAB PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Northern Troops Continue Push Forward Toward Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Northern Troops Continue Push Forward Toward Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ministry Statement on Battles' Progress </H4>

<F P=102> JN1605203494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1900 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1605203494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible military source at the Defense 
Ministry has stated the following: 
  With God Almighty's support and guidance to the courageous, 
loyal heroes in our valiant Armed Forces, the forces of 
protecting unity and Constitutional legitimacy, and with the 
willpower of the valiant fighters, units of the Armed Forces 
continued to fulfill their combat tasks against the 
secessionist, rebellious forces in the Socialist Party 
leadership, and those who are following its orders and who lost 
their willpower and logic and all sense of responsibility, 
inflicting heavy losses on them on all axes and sectors. 
  On the Shabwah axis, our troops completed the mopping up of 
Bayhan district from the elements of secession and apostasy in 
cooperation with the honorable citizens of Bayhan district. Our 
forces yesterday regained control of Mulhim Brigade with its 
heavy and medium weapons, including 22 tanks, five katyusha 
BM-21 vehicles, a number of armed crews, and a large quantity of 
ammunition. A number of officers, NCO's, and soldiers from the 
Mulhim Brigade joined the legitimacy troops, announcing their 
adherence to unity, democracy, and Constitutional legitimacy. 
  On the Abyan axis, our Armed Forces continued their advance 
and are now closing on al-'Alam point. 
  On the al-'Anad-al-Hawtah axis, the 14th Battalion of the 
22d 
Infantry Brigade, with all its ordnance, joined the forces of 
Constitutional legitimacy. All members of the battalion 
announced their refusal to fight with the forces of rebellion 
and the gang of apostasy and secession in the Socialist Party 
leadership. 
  At the same time, the forces of legitimacy continued their 
advance toward al-'Anad Base and took control of the area in 
which the base is located on the Ta'izz-Aden-al-Dali' 
crossroads. They then completed their seige of the base from 
all the directions to allow the elements deceived by the gang of 
apostasy and secession at the Socialist Party leadership the 
opportunity to join the forces of Constitutional legitimacy. 
  Today, our Air Force pilots carried out their missions in 
the 
battlefield, achieving the set objectives. All planes returned 
safely to base. 
  Our Armed Forces units continue to receive in succession the 
officers, NCO's, and soldiers who are joining the Armed Forces, 
the forces for protecting unity and Constitutional legitimacy. 
They voiced their rejection of the instructions and hegemony of 
the secessionist, rebellious forces and their denunciation of 
that gang and its major crimes against the people, the Armed 
Forces and security troops. They also expressed their readiness 
to sacrifice for the sake or unity and to protect Constitutional 
legitimacy and democracy in the country. 
  Here we underline the dark fate which the secessionist 
rebels 
must meet thanks to the heroism of the entire Yemeni people, 
headed by those who take pride in belonging to the Armed Forces 
and security troops, who defend the people and the homeland and 
its eternal achievements, and who confront any one who may be 
tempted to infringe on them. They are, and will always remain, 
the men protecting the lives of all citizens and the homeland's 
security and stability and protectors of property, freedoms, 
rights, and honor in all governorates and cities. 
  Those who circulate lies and spread false rumors will only 
fail. 
  In the name of God, the compassionate, the merciful: And 
soon will the unjust assailants know what vicissitudes their 
affairs will take. [Koranic verse] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

