<H3> <TI>   Northern Troops Continue Push Forward Toward Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Northern Troops Continue Push Forward Toward Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    North Captures South's Air Base of al-'Anad </H4>

<F P=102> NC1605152094 Paris AFP in English 1510 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1605152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, May 16 (AFP) -- Northern troops on Monday [16 
May] captured the south's main air base of Al-'Anad which 
controls a key highway leading to the southern stronghold of 
Aden, the official Yemeni news agency SABA said. 
  The agency, run by the north, said Salih's troops were 
"mopping up the last pockets of the rebel forces in Al-'Anad 
base," around 60 kilometres (35 miles) north of the port city. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

