<H3> <TI>   Northern Troops Continue Push Forward Toward Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Northern Troops Continue Push Forward Toward Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Military Situation `Decided' in Salih's Favor </H4>

<F P=102> JN1705112494 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1100 GMT 17 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1705112494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shaykh 'Abdallah al-Ahmar, speaker of the Yemeni 
House of Representatives, has asserted that the forces loyal to 
President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih have decided the military 
situation in their favor following the seizure of the southern 
major base of al-'Anad. In a statement to the Qatari News Agency 
over the phone, al-Ahmar said that the crisis has ended, 
affirming that the southern units, which have joined the 
northerners, are now fighting against the rebellious forces in 
the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] led by 'Ali Salim al-Bid. 
  Al-Ahmar rejected the YSP's call to form a national 
salvation 
government and said: This means nobody is running the country's 
affairs. 

</TEXT>

