<F P=100> ARAB PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   League Delegation Departs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    League Delegation Departs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1705143094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1705143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An Arab League delegation led by brother Major 
General Muhammad Sa'id Bayraqdar, Arab League assistant 
secretary general for military affairs, left Sanaa today 
following a visit to our country. 
  During the visit, Maj. Gen. Bayraqdar conveyed a message to 
brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the 
Presidential Council and supreme commander of the Armed Forces, 
from Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid. 
  In a statement to the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', brother 
Bayraqdar explained that the brother Presidential Council 
chairman yesterday briefed the delegation on the Yemeni 
situation and on the great opportunities and concessions given 
to the [Yemeni] Socialist Party [YSP] in order to safeguard 
Yemeni unity. However, none of these achieved any result, Salih 
added. Thus, the possibility of cease-fire is ruled out unless 
the YSP elements which rebelled against legitimacy and which are 
responsible for these events either leave the country or 
surrender to legitimacy. 
  Bayraqdar pointed out that the brother Presidential Council 
chairman and other officials in Sanaa welcomed the role the Arab 
League is playing. 
  The delegation was seen off by brother [word indistinct] [? 
Sami], deputy head of the Arab Homeland Department at the 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs; a representative of the 
Presidential Council Protocol Office; and brother 'Ata Harun, 
Egyptian ambassador in Sanaa. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

