<H3> <TI>   President Salih Appoints New Abyan Governor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Salih Appoints New Abyan Governor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1405063594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1405063594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Presidential Decree No. 23, issued by the Presidency in </F>
Sanaa on 13 May] 
  [Text] The Presidential Council chairman, taking cognizance 
of the Constitution of the Republic of Yemen and Law No. 52 of 
1991 concerning the Local Administration Law, and at the 
recommendation of the acting prime minister, and following the 
approval of the Council of Ministers and the Presidential 
Council, decides the following: 
  Article 1: Brother 'Ali Shaykh 'Umar shall be appointed 
governor of Abyan Governorate. 
  Article 2: This decree shall go into effect as of the day of 
its issuance. It shall be published in the official gazette. 
  Issued at the Presidency in Sanaa on 3 Dhu al-Hijjah 1414 
Hegira, corresponding to 13 May 1994. 
  [Signed] Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
Presidential Council chairman; Dr. Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar, the 
acting prime minister 

</TEXT>

