<H3> <TI>   Higher Council Discusses Supply Policy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Higher Council Discusses Supply Policy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1605134294 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1605134294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Higher Council for Economic and Oil Affairs met 
today under Acting Prime Minister Dr. Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar. 
  At the outset of the meeting, the Council reviewed its 
agenda, and then discussed the supply policy under the current 
circumstances and made the necessary decisions to guarantee the 
availability of foodstuffs in all the republic's governorates 
for the set prices, especially since these commodities are 
available in sufficient quantities to meet the republic's needs. 

</TEXT>

