<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Political Party Condemns `Departure' From Legitimacy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Political Party Condemns `Departure' From Legitimacy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1605184794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1605184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Executive Committee of the League of the Sons of 
Yemen Party [LSYP] has condemned any attempt to depart from the 
principles of Yemeni unity, the Republic of Yemen, the 
democratic gains, the political pluralism, the multiparty 
system, and the constitutional legitimacy, which is represented 
by the Presidential Council that was elected by the elected 
legislative authority. The party views such a departure as a 
departure from the Yemeni people's consensus and will. 
  The statement issued by the committee today asserts that the 
LSYP adheres to the Yemeni unity, views it as a destiny, and 
believes in democracy, political pluralism, the multiparty 
system, and constitutional legitimacy, which was established by 
the Yemeni people's consensus and in light of the general 
elections that were held on 27 April before the eyes of the 
entire world, including all the fraternal Arab countries. 
  The statement expresses the Executive Committee's rejection 
of any statement, issued in the name of the league without its 
approval, and which conflicts with the party's positions stated 
in this statement. It also stresses that assigning certain 
tasks by the party to its representatives from the national 
opposition bloc is temporary and not permanent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

